= Weekly meal plan

- Courses : Every 2 saturdays

Sunday
    Fried food day : fried cheese + fried chicken/fish
        + 6 eggs + rest steak haché (as needed)
    every 2 weeks fish : frozen cabillaud + some fruit de mer (noix de saint jaques, crevettes, crabe..)
    every 2 weeks chicken : pilons

Monday : maquereau (conserve, surgelé)

Thuesday : cotes agneau (Go to boucher here)
wednsday : entrecote/faux filet + 200-300g lamb liver
thursday : cotes agneau
friday : entrecote/faux filet (Go to boucher here)
     + sometimes 4 merguez or some abats
saturday : cotes agneau 

6 eggs/day
    soft boiled
    medium boiled
    fried whole
    scrambled
        + butter
        + cheese
        + some meat : merguez, crevette, jambon, steak...

Steak haché + some cheese (fake cheddar, tomme savoie, etc)
    Fill in the blanks


100-150g cheese/day
    AOP/IGP lait cru : to eat raw
    AOP/IGP pasteurisé : steaks, eggs, fried
    other cheeses : fried, steaks


- Cost : Less than 450e/month
- Nutrition :
    Omega 3 :
        Worst case : 55(makerel) + 15 (lamb) = 70g/week (1.54:1)
        Best case : 55(makerel) + 15 (lamb) +  7(cheese) = 77 (1.69:1)
    Omega 6 :
         5/2(chicken) + 5(beef) + 6(steak haché) + 25(eggs) + 7(cheese) = 45.5









------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


600g chicken every 2 weeks
    fried dumsticks, thighs
    fried wings (use only protein powder)
    fried nuggets
    fried tenders
        thighs : chicken fingers, seared with skin
            https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TDUcQhOzO1Q
    cuisses poulet roti

500g fish every 2 weeks
    oven baked : sardines, maqueraux
    fried fish : cabillaud, merlu, sole, merlan, others

300-500g frozen seafood
    fruits de mer : crevettes, gambas, noix saint-jaques, encornet, poulpe, moules, crabe
        plancha + some sauce
    fried fish : cabillaud



6 eggs/day
    soft boiled
    medium boiled
    fried whole
    scrambled
        + butter
        + cheese
        + creme fraiche
        + some meat : merguez, crevette, jambon...

1.5kg agneau : gigot tranches, cotes
    sometimes : poitrine
3 tranches 300g entrecote/faux filet

1kg steak haché to fill the blanks
    + cheddar on top

100-150g cheese/day
    AOP/IGP lait cru : to eat raw
    AOP/IGP pasteurisé : sauce, with eggs
    other cheeses : fried
    cheddar + fake cheddar : for steaks

lamb liver : 200g every 2 weeks
    or buy one liver and freeze

Sometimes:
    fressure/abats : rognons, poumon, coeur
    tete agneau
    merguez

---
cost /w : 13.65 + 11.35 + 10.5 + 17 + 8 + 28,5 + 15.3 = 105
    = 450e/month
